hape[1])), fill_colors[:, :-1]))\ndef get_num_colors(input_colors: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    return len(np.unique(input_colors))", "holes": {"fill_column": "fill in ith row (output_grid.shape[0] - i)'s column of the output_grid", "pad_fill_colors": "if the fill colors length <= output_grid.shape[0], cat a black pixel before it. If greater, cat a black pixel before it can delete its last pixel", "get_num_colors": "Get the number of colors in the input_colors"}}
